### Revenue Analysis

The Company’s revenue has grown steadily over the past three years, driven by increased sales volume and price realizations. The Dairy segment contributes the majority of the Company’s revenue, while the Ice Cream segment has shown significant growth in recent years.

### EBITDA Analysis

The Company’s EBITDA has also grown in line with revenue, reflecting improved operational efficiency and cost management. The EBITDA margin has remained relatively stable, indicating the Company’s ability to maintain profitability despite fluctuations in raw material prices.

### Net Profit Analysis

The Company’s net profit has increased over the past three years, driven by higher revenue and improved EBITDA margins. The Company has also benefited from tax benefits and other non-operating income.

### Capital Expenditure

The Company has undertaken significant capital expenditure in recent years to expand its production capacity and modernize its facilities. The Company plans to continue investing in capital expenditure to support its growth strategy.

### Debt Profile

The Company has a moderate level of debt, which is primarily used to fund working capital requirements and capital expenditure. The Company has a strong debt service coverage ratio and a healthy interest coverage ratio.

### Liquidity Position

The Company has a strong liquidity position, with sufficient cash and cash equivalents to meet its short-term obligations. The Company also has access to bank credit facilities, which provide additional financial flexibility.

